@Cesar - The growth of the largest 2 companies in shipbuilding has really been phenomenal. The top 2 companies in that industry have really taken over!  

I notice, however, that even though shipbuilding is increasingly being controlled by 2 companies, it doesn't indicate that more ships are being built than airplanes, for example. It just shows us that within that industry, the top 2 companies are "taking over" that field.

Do you think it is good or bad for only 2 companies to "control" any particular industry?

@Maria - Interesting noticing. Although the top 2 companies have acquired a larger portion of the tobacco market, we do not know (from this graph), how the tobacco industry has grown (or decreased) compared to other markets. 

Any idea what the top 2 tobacco companies are? Identifying them could help to begin to discover why they have gained such a large portion of that market. 

Nice noticing and wondering, and I like your headline!

@CCDMJD - Yes! I also wonder what the 2 biggest companies are for each industry. It could be fun to guess this and then look it up online.

The top 2 companies in the tire manufacturing industry is losing its monopoly. Do you think this is a good thing or a bad thing?

Love your title!

@Dakota - Welcome to the conversation Dakota Group! 

Great noticing and wondering, and I love your title! Many of these industries are seeing the top 2 companies really "making their mark" by gaining in market share. 

I also wonder what is going on with the tire manufacturing industry. Maybe your group could determine what the two largest companies are in the tire manufacturing industry? I wonder what is going on with those companies that is causing them to lose market share.
